      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.31083/j.fbs1604021"
      },
      "sc:description": "Alternative polyadenylation (APA) is one of the important post- transcriptional regulation mechanisms which occurs in most human genes. InPAS facilitates the discovery of novel APA sites and the differential usage of APA sites from RNA-Seq data. It leverages cleanUpdTSeq to fine tune identified APA sites by removing false sites.",
